body:
Given the following code: [playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=5c4a1be2ec2d4e51abeb8ab5d60fc9d9)
```rust
trait TSigned {}
impl TSigned for i32 {}

trait TList {
    type Element;
}
trait TArray {}

struct ArrayListI32 {}
impl TList for ArrayListI32 {
    type Element = i32;
}
impl TArray for ArrayListI32 {}

struct ArrayListU32 {}
impl TList for ArrayListU32 {
    type Element = u32;
}
impl TArray for ArrayListU32 {}


trait TList2D {
    type Row: TList;
}

struct List2D {}
impl TList2D for List2D {
    type Row = ArrayListI32;
}


fn main() {
    fn2(fn1());
}

fn fn1() -> impl TList2D<Row = impl TArray> {
    List2D {}
}

fn fn2<T>(some: T)
where
    T: TList2D,
    <T::Row as TList>::Element: TSigned,
{
}
```

The current output is:
```
error[[E0277]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/error-index.html#E0277): the trait bound `impl TArray: TList` is not satisfied
  --> src/main.rs:33:5
   |
33 |     fn2(fn1());
   |     ^^^ the trait `TList` is not implemented for `impl TArray`
   |
   = help: the following other types implement trait `TList`:
             ArrayListI32
             ArrayListU32
```

However, `impl TArray: TList` is not the trait bound that is not being satisfied. It is `<impl TArray as TList>::ELement: TSigned` that's not being satisfied.

Further more, help actually suggest `ArrayListU32` as a possible replacement for `impl TArray`, even though `u32` does not implement `TSigned`.

Once you change the return type to `impl TList2D<Row = impl TArray + TList>` the error message makes much more sense:
```
error[[E0277]](https://doc.rust-lang.org/stable/error-index.html#E0277): the trait bound `<impl TList + TArray as TList>::Element: TSigned` is not satisfied
  --> src/main.rs:33:5
   |
33 |     fn2(fn1());
   |     ^^^ the trait `TSigned` is not implemented for `<impl TList + TArray as TList>::Element`
   |
   = help: the trait `TSigned` is implemented for `i32`
note: required by a bound in `fn2`
  --> src/main.rs:43:33
   |
40 | fn fn2<T>(some: T)
   |    --- required by a bound in this
...
43 |     <T::Row as TList>::Element: TSigned,
   |
```

However, sometimes `TList` is private to another crate, making adding `TList` to the return type impossible which then makes the error message much harder to decrypt.

It would be nice if the second error message would be shown without having to add `TList` to the return type. Perhaps showing `<impl TArray as TList>::Element: TSigned` instead to match what was written as the return type.
